---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const page = {
  title: "Fall Lawn Recovery Guide | Edwards Landscape Group",
  description: "Use aeration, overseeding, and balanced nutrition to help your lawn rebound after summer stress."
};
---

<BaseLayout {...page}>
<main>
      <section
        class="page-hero article-hero"
        style="background-image: url('../images/FallCleanUp_Service.jpg');"
        aria-label="Fall lawn recovery hero"
      >
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row align-items-end">
            <div class="col-lg-8 hero-content-block">
              <div class="hero-kicker">Seasonal playbook</div>
              <h1>Fall lawn recovery guide for thicker spring growth</h1>
              <p class="article-subtitle">
                Restore compacted soil, add seed where summer heat thinned turf, and feed your lawn so it greens up sooner.
              </p>
              <div class="article-meta">
                <span>By Edwards Landscape Group</span>
                <span>&bull;</span>
                <span>Updated September 5, 2024</span>
                <span>&bull;</span>
                <span>7 min read</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="article-container" aria-labelledby="article-heading">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="article-layout">
            <aside class="article-toc" aria-label="On this page">
              <h2>Quick navigation</h2>
              <ol>
                <li><a href="#evaluate">Evaluate summer stress</a></li>
                <li><a href="#aerate">Aerate compacted soil</a></li>
                <li><a href="#seed">Overseed bare areas</a></li>
                <li><a href="#feed">Feed and water</a></li>
                <li><a href="#cleanup">Finish with cleanup</a></li>
              </ol>
            </aside>

            <article class="article-content" id="article-heading">
              <p>
                Fall is the best time to reset cool-season grasses in Virginia. Soil is still warm enough for quick germination,
                nights are cooler, and weeds slow down. Following this TruGreen-inspired sequence ensures new seed takes root and
                existing turf rebounds before winter dormancy.
              </p>

              <h2 id="evaluate">1. Evaluate summer stress</h2>
              <p>
                Walk the yard to spot thin areas, compaction from foot traffic, or drought stress. Note any fungus damage so you
                can adjust watering and plan fungicide if needed.
              </p>

              <h2 id="aerate">2. Aerate compacted soil</h2>
              <p>
                Core aeration opens space for roots and improves nutrient uptake. Our crews run cross patterns for even coverage
                and flag irrigation heads beforehand to protect your system.
              </p>
              <div class="article-callout">
                <h3>Tip</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">Leave cores on the lawnâ€”they break down fast and topdress the soil surface.</p>
              </div>

              <h2 id="seed">3. Overseed bare areas</h2>
              <p>
                Spread premium seed immediately after aeration so it can fall into the open cores. We match seed to your sun and
                shade conditions for even color and density.
              </p>
              <ul class="pill-list">
                <li>Shade-tolerant blends for tree-lined yards</li>
                <li>Sun-loving mixes for open turf</li>
                <li>Starter fertilizer to boost germination</li>
              </ul>

              <h2 id="feed">4. Feed and water</h2>
              <p>
                A balanced fertilizer with slow-release nitrogen fuels root growth without forcing tall top growth before winter.
                Water lightly twice a day for the first two weeks, then reduce to deeper, less frequent cycles.
              </p>

              <h2 id="cleanup">5. Finish with cleanup</h2>
              <p>
                End the season with a leaf cleanup and one final mowing at a slightly lower height. This prevents matting under
                snow and keeps air moving through the canopy.
              </p>

              <div class="article-cta">
                <div>
                  <p class="eyebrow mb-1">Want pro help?</p>
                  <h3 class="mb-2">Bundle aeration, overseeding, and cleanup</h3>
                  <p class="mb-0">We time each visit for your property so new seed thrives and winter arrives with healthy turf.</p>
                </div>
                <a class="btn btn-primary" href="../contact.html">Schedule fall services</a>
              </div>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
